						Administrative Procedure Act (Chapter 3.5 (commencing with Section 11340) of Part 1 of Division 3 of Title 2 of the Government Code), the Office of Land Use and Climate Innovation may implement, interpret, or make specific this subdivision without taking any regulatory action.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(k) This section shall remain in effect only until January 1, 2040, and as of that date is repealed.</div></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s30.41597562252827414"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SEC. 3.</h3> Section 992 is added to the Streets and Highways Code, to read:</div><div><div id="id_315BCA19-3F13-4023-A0D1-BAA8AC6E5812"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">992.</h6> (a) <font color="#B30000"><strike>(1)<span class="EnSpace"/></strike></font>A county shall not hold a community input meeting to reconsider, delay, or prevent implementation of a proposed pedestrian or bicycle safety project for a county highway<font color="#B30000"><strike>
