						traffic-calming measures, bicycle facilities, pedestrian facilities, street reconfigurations, signal modifications, and quick-build or pilot projects.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) “Terminate” means canceling or materially delaying a project before construction or ordering the removal of an already constructed project. “Terminate” does not include the temporary removal of a pedestrian or bicycle safety project for construction,<font color="#B30000"><strike> for upgrades from</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> removal of</i></font> quick-builds or pilot<font color="#B30000"><strike> programs to permanent infrastructure, or</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> programs, removal of a
						bikeway to upgrade the facility, reconstruction or restriping of a bikeway that maintains its current class, or removal of a pedestrian or bicycle safety project</i></font> under emergency conditions.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) “Traffic-calming measure” has the same meaning as that term is used in paragraph (3) of subdivision (i) of Section 21455.9 of the Vehicle Code.</div></p></div></div></div></div><div id="s80.9728397124362793"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SEC. 8.</h3> Section 1816 is added to the Streets and Highways Code, to read:</div><div><div id="id_FF754788-F481-46BF-A62D-B89A1CBC399B"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">1816.</h6> (a) If the legislative body of a city establishes a process for residents of the city to submit a petition to request the installation of a traffic-calming measure on a street or highway, the legislative body shall not require the petition to contain the signatures of more than a majority of the total number of persons whose residences are located, in whole or in part, within 1,000 feet of the proposed traffic-calming measure, as measured along the centerline of a street or highway or combination of streets and highways.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) For purposes of this section, “traffic-calming measure” has the same meaning as that term is used in paragraph (3) of subdivision (i) of
						Section 21455.9 of the Vehicle Code.</div></p></div></div></div></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><caml:BillSection id="id_86FFCAB2-A70E-4A76-BBB9-2CA828FC516F"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 9.</caml:Num><caml:ActionLine action="IS_ADDED" xlink:href="urn:caml:codes:SHC:caml#xpointer(%2Fcaml%3ALawDoc%2Fcaml%3ACode%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'DIVISION'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'13.'%5D%2Fcaml%3ALawHeading%5B%40type%3D'PART'%20and%20caml%3ANum%3D'2.'%5D)" xlink:label="fractionType: LAW_SPREAD||commencingWith: 12000" xlink:type="locator">Part 2 (commencing with Section 12000) is added to Division 13 of the <caml:DocName>Streets and Highways Code</caml:DocName>, to read:</caml:ActionLine><caml:Fragment><caml:LawHeading id="id_959C0429-6EE8-4455-B605-53EBE07998B9" type="PART"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>2.</caml:Num><caml:LawHeadingVersion id="id_B9C2E86B-DF9E-40E1-B565-312A30E06B64"><caml:LawHeadingText>Pedestrian Mall Law of 2026</caml:LawHeadingText></caml:LawHeadingVersion><caml:LawHeading id="id_063BBEAD-6922-4E8E-A1C2-BDDB79BDA871" type="CHAPTER"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>1.</caml:Num><caml:LawHeadingVersion id="id_A326C456-2709-4C0A-8F4F-109FF34F0DA4"><caml:LawHeadingText>General Provisions and Definitions</caml:LawHeadingText></caml:LawHeadingVersion><caml:LawSection id="id_FE82E593-818F-4CFC-A4E6-D53DC7E67848"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12000.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_5E6BD340-9DF0-4280-842D-C06E2BA683FA"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>This part shall be known, and may be cited, as the Pedestrian Mall Law of 2026.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_E4D20434-AD82-4671-BB82-C82A21EE97AC"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12001.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_108DEC78-67A4-4E55-80C1-DEF29A84C2C0"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>Unless the context otherwise requires, the definitions contained in this chapter shall govern the construction of this part.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_C8CCC5A5-86EB-4C7F-A602-D2D63C7DB96D"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12002.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_709018B5-BAA1-4A90-8B49-745AA74D5125"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>“City” includes every county, city, and city and county within this state. “The city” means the particular county, city, or city and county, acting pursuant to this part.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_3E792945-0D47-4F45-BFF8-53E4A9684E83"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12003.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_CDBAB393-9CE3-43FE-9743-DEA94A142870"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>“City street,” as used with regard to streets located within a city or city and county, means a street located within the city or city and county, except a freeway or county highway, as defined in Sections 23.5 and 25. “City street,” as used with regard to streets located
							 within a county, means a street located within the county, except a freeway, as defined in Section 23.5.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_8C1A4C52-ECF7-4BC4-9913-398D877E7D1C"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12004.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_D09DF125-4A22-48C0-B406-5C0581E5316B"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>“Improvements” include, but are not limited to, paving, sidewalks, curbs, gutters, sewers, drainage works, street lighting facilities, fire protection facilities, flood protection facilities, water distribution facilities, retaining walls, landscaping, tree planting, statuary, fountains, decorative structures, benches, restrooms, childcare facilities, display facilities, information booths, public assembly facilities, improvements necessary or convenient for a covered air-conditioned mall, and other structures, works, or improvements necessary or convenient to serve members of the public using the applicable pedestrian mall, including the reconstruction or relocation of existing city-owned works and improvements or facilities on the city
							 streets. “Improvement” does not include vehicular parking facilities.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_56CC72D0-0098-41AD-B079-AAFFA08F64AB"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12005.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_92E25BF2-4B7F-4B29-9E8B-00438962D61D"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>“Legislative body” means the legislative body of the city.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_64155528-4847-4DCE-8B50-ED5BA1789BFD"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12006.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_8401415F-72BD-4E3D-9643-B026D1DD69F8"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>“Pedestrian mall” means one or more “city streets,” or portions thereof, on which vehicular traffic is or is to be restricted in whole or in part and which is or is to be used exclusively or primarily for pedestrian travel.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_914B6EAD-4F97-4B8D-BBD4-DC99D21FC661"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12007.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_55BF4564-FE2A-4EB0-A7B9-197052281310"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>“Street” means any public street, road, highway, alley, lane, court, way, or place of any nature open to the use of the public.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:LawHeading><caml:LawHeading id="id_773A7E0F-3655-4A6F-9CFC-3CCC6462E599" type="CHAPTER"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>2.</caml:Num><caml:LawHeadingVersion id="id_7C31DABE-1B4D-4E88-852E-4C25EDC0925A"><caml:LawHeadingText>Purposes and Powers</caml:LawHeadingText></caml:LawHeadingVersion><caml:LawSection id="id_E85F4711-45C3-4D87-960E-619281B37D07"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12100.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_C55A8A47-48D3-416A-87D3-F8445B685DC7"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The Legislature hereby finds and declares all of the following:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>In certain areas of cities in the state, there is a need to separate pedestrian travel from vehicular travel.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>That separation is necessary to support local commerce, promote civic gatherings, encourage cultural activities, protect the public safety, or otherwise serve the public interest and convenience.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>That objective can, in part, be accomplished by the establishment of pedestrian malls pursuant to this part.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_C0FA7895-0C34-4F23-968E-FC0159AC6FB0"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12101.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_429B34E4-377D-4E48-AC33-4A621B6B8802"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>A legislative body may do all of the following:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>Establish pedestrian malls.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>Prohibit, in whole or in part, vehicular traffic on a pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>Construct on city streets that have been or will be established as a pedestrian mall improvements of any kind or nature necessary or convenient to the operation of the city streets as a pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(d)<span class="EnSpace"/>Pay, from general funds of the city or any other available moneys, the whole or any portion of the cost of improvements constructed
							 pursuant to subdivision (c).</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(e)<span class="EnSpace"/>To do any and all other acts or things necessary or convenient for the accomplishment of the purposes of this part.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_9A4A74FB-CED5-4F86-8D1A-651B94538F35"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12102.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_941DD876-24DD-40E8-ACA3-96A7C2D3B445"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>A city may not establish a pedestrian mall on a state highway pursuant to Section 12200 until the city receives approval from the department pursuant to Chapter 4 (commencing with Section 12300).</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_EDD09FA1-C01E-4DD0-8925-B6D9C712B3F2"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12103.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_499DBFF4-17C7-4AB7-B343-312D4CC3D9B0"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>(1)<span class="EnSpace"/>A legislative body may acquire, by gift, purchase, eminent domain, or otherwise, land, real property, or rights-of-way that will become part of a city street established as a pedestrian mall or that will otherwise be used by the city as part of, or for purposes connected with, a pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>Land, real property, or rights-of-way acquired pursuant to paragraph (1) may be improved in the same manner as city streets may be improved pursuant to subdivision (c) of Section
							 12101.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>A legislative body may make improvements on city streets adjacent to the pedestrian mall where those improvements are necessary or convenient to the operation of the mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_C4303A95-C454-49B1-9447-B57FBDC9CF7F"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12104.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_382D2519-22E1-4EEF-A1AE-7D4930AFEC17"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The powers granted pursuant to this part to prohibit, in whole or in part, vehicular traffic on a city street shall be in addition to, and not limited by, the powers granted by Section 21101 of the Vehicle Code or by any other law.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_152DA144-9865-4947-B2BF-73842008251F"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12105.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_15E1ED0C-4714-42FD-BAB8-DDB7841A4234"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>This part shall be liberally construed to the end that its purpose may be effective.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>This part does not affect any other law relating to the same or similar subject, but provides an alternative procedure for the subject to which it relates. When proceedings are taken under this part, its provisions only shall apply. The Special Assessment Investigation, Limitation and Majority Protest Act of 1931 (Division 4 (commencing with Section 2800)) shall not apply to any proceedings taken
							 under any other law for the improvement of a pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:LawHeading><caml:LawHeading id="id_F4C0CF17-FFC0-4DB7-8871-964DE945BD12" type="CHAPTER"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>3.</caml:Num><caml:LawHeadingVersion id="id_FC7D3D2A-17D1-47C3-A863-B7EF91492B2D"><caml:LawHeadingText>Establishment and Improvement of a Pedestrian Mall</caml:LawHeadingText></caml:LawHeadingVersion><caml:LawSection id="id_E833EE78-643E-4DAD-9F63-33B795DCB6CA"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12200.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_0C731E8F-4ACC-4BAD-BFF9-3E7558157A01"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>A legislative body may adopt, following a public hearing, a resolution or ordinance to establish a pedestrian mall if it determines that the public interest and convenience requires the establishment of the pedestrian mall. The resolution or ordinance shall contain all of the following:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>The following findings:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(1)<span class="EnSpace"/>A determination that the closure or traffic restriction leaves a sufficient portion of the streets in the surrounding area for other public uses, including vehicular, pedestrian, and bicycle traffic.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>A determination that the closure will create a
							 public benefit to local commerce, civic gatherings, cultural activities, public safety, or otherwise serve the public interest and convenience.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>A general description of the pedestrian mall, including the city streets, or portions of city streets, that are to be established as a pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>Rules and regulations prohibiting vehicular traffic, in whole or in part, on the pedestrian mall. If vehicular traffic is proposed to be prohibited only in part, the resolution or ordinance shall also contain a general statement of the exceptions proposed to be made. The resolution or ordinance may include any of the following exceptions:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(1)<span class="EnSpace"/>Exceptions in favor of public, emergency, utility, and other classes of
							 vehicles.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>Exceptions in favor of all or certain classes of vehicles during certain days or during portions of days.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(3)<span class="EnSpace"/>Exceptions of any other kind or nature.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(d)<span class="EnSpace"/>Any additional rules and regulations pertaining to the interpretation, operation, and enforcement of the rules and regulations described in subdivision (c), and otherwise pertaining to the use, operation, maintenance, and control of the pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_581A510E-7FBB-4B83-B94E-EB4B2145E022"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12201.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_E787C02F-5ADC-45A9-BF9A-53D41FDF52B2"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The city shall provide notice of the public hearing described in Section 12200 in accordance with Chapter 2.7 (commencing with Section 65090) of Division 1 of Title 7 of the Government Code.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_CCD9A990-1B11-4A46-9913-852CBC2E2CF0"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12202.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_DD3CC2D7-582D-404F-8FA3-E576DBA33E3B"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>A city may initiate the process to establish a pedestrian mall or may initiate the process following an application by a business, educational institution, or other entity.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>Receipt of an application pursuant to subdivision (a) shall not obligate a city to initiate the process to establish a pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_A5147128-BFFF-447D-9756-40E69B4C1E0A"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12203.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_1BF8215C-6BC1-47CE-97B4-0550BDE0EF3A"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>If, in connection with the initial establishment of a pedestrian mall, a legislative body proposes to make any improvements, the resolution or ordinance described in Section 12200 shall also contain all of the following:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(1)<span class="EnSpace"/>A general description of the improvements proposed to be made. The description may be made in any manner permitted or provided in any law under which the improvements are to be made or financed.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>A general statement of the source or sources of moneys proposed to be used to pay the costs and expenses of the improvements.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(3)<span class="EnSpace"/>If all or any part of the improvements are proposed to be
							 made or financed under the Improvement Act of 1911 (Division 7 (commencing with Section 5000)), the Municipal Improvement Act of 1913 (Division 12 (commencing with Section 10000)), or similar special assessment law, a statement as to what law is proposed to be used.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>A legislative body may allow private businesses use of the pedestrian mall and may allow those private businesses to make improvements to the pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_69806248-A480-457C-91F4-4ECDF9928781"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12204.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_EB713B5C-31E2-4A52-A6E6-B351858B4AD2"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>A legislative body shall install and maintain signage that clearly designates the boundaries of the pedestrian mall and related improvements and that clearly states the applicable restriction on the use of vehicles within the pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_07D8F5F6-97C1-4D41-9C53-B74DD363CEF5"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12205.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_B1838429-6DD8-4013-B8C6-61705C9A7239"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>Before the adoption of the resolution or ordinance pursuant to Section 12200, a legislative body may allow a pilot or phased pedestrian mall project pursuant to any other law that permits temporary street closures, including, but not limited to, Section 21101 of the Vehicle Code.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>If a pilot or phased pedestrian mall project is proposed pursuant to subdivision (a) for establishment on a state highway, the legislative body shall obtain approval from the department before allowing the project.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_1A3BC6DF-E894-403F-A6C7-CAC974E3EC43"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12206.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_4F5804EF-45D0-4E76-98A8-F4F819B98BE0"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>A legislative body may only expand, reduce, or rescind a pedestrian mall upon adoption of a resolution or ordinance, after a public meeting, on the matter, and, if the pedestrian mall is located on a state highway, upon approval by the department.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>(1)<span class="EnSpace"/>The act of rescinding a pedestrian mall does not require a
							 city to return the street to its prior condition unless the pedestrian mall is located on a state highway and the department requires otherwise pursuant to an agreement entered into pursuant to Chapter 4 (commencing with Section 12300).</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>If the pedestrian mall
							 is located on a state highway, the department may require periodic review of the pedestrian mall to evaluate its impacts on safety, mobility, and local access.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_83163D6B-2EE5-4503-AD84-DB541777DD14"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12207.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_C0C2999E-20F9-4918-9E82-8BF4A6671371"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The establishment of a pedestrian mall is consistent with the public access requirements of the California Coastal Act of 1976 (Division 20 (commencing with Section 30000) of the Public Resources Code).</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:LawHeading><caml:LawHeading id="id_EF652676-CE71-4620-9FF6-6373E3F096D7" type="CHAPTER"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>4.</caml:Num><caml:LawHeadingVersion id="id_27F03C36-9B0E-41D8-97A7-16CCFB4A4BF2"><caml:LawHeadingText>Pedestrian Malls on State Highways</caml:LawHeadingText></caml:LawHeadingVersion><caml:LawSection id="id_5FC8EB7F-A584-4940-AE2B-336EE0C9915E"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12300.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_E3C83371-E11A-4AEC-B01D-9C5DF1337677"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>A city in which a state highway is located may initiate a request to establish a pedestrian mall on that state highway, or a portion of that state highway, pursuant to this chapter.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>A request pursuant to subdivision (a) shall be initiated by adoption of a resolution of the legislative body of the city.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>A request may be initiated by the legislative body of the city on its own motion or following receipt of an application by a business, business improvement district, educational institution, or other entity.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(d)<span class="EnSpace"/>Receipt of an
							 application shall not obligate the legislative body to initiate a request.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_9FB6DB7F-65E1-45A0-9E50-AC1BF71F55E8"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12301.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_2F0EC916-A46A-413A-9775-2DBD1162DE66"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>A state highway, or portion of a state highway, shall not be established as a pedestrian mall pursuant to this chapter unless the legislative body finds, and the department concurs, that the state highway functions as a main street.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>For purposes of this section, “main street” means a segment of a state highway that primarily serves local access, commerce, or community activity.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_FFB82D5C-9454-47DE-BB33-8848132E0A40"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12302.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_CB1D35B8-EB5D-4639-92B7-D8086E149904"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>Upon adoption of a resolution pursuant to Section 12300, the legislative body may submit a formal request to the department to approve the establishment of the pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>The request shall include all of the following information:</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(1)<span class="EnSpace"/>A general description of the proposed pedestrian mall, including the affected segment of the state highway.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)<span class="EnSpace"/>The findings required pursuant to Section 12200.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(3)<span class="EnSpace"/>A traffic analysis demonstrating that the proposed closure or restriction will not
							 unreasonably impede regional or intercity travel and that sufficient alternative routes exist.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(4)<span class="EnSpace"/>A description of proposed improvements, if any.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(5)<span class="EnSpace"/>A description of how emergency access, transit operations, and goods movement will be maintained or accommodated.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(6)<span class="EnSpace"/>Any other information required by the department.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_E642550C-EFB0-4E37-A33C-D25B94D2C7CC"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12303.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_0C117D67-284E-4F92-924F-AB715EF764E8"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>The department may approve, approve with conditions, or deny a request submitted pursuant to Section 12302.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>The department may adopt guidelines to determine the process for approving or denying a request to establish a pedestrian mall on a state highway.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)<span class="EnSpace"/>The department may impose reasonable conditions on an approval, including conditions related to design, operations, maintenance, and ongoing performance monitoring.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_D9B77C45-AA9B-4122-9F96-137BD887B6EB"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12304.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_8588D941-1FE9-48F9-9C87-AC22A1DFD1F2"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>Following approval by the department, the legislative body may adopt a resolution or ordinance pursuant to Section 12200 to establish the pedestrian mall.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>The resolution or ordinance shall be consistent with any conditions imposed by the department pursuant to this chapter.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_D4215BA6-FEFA-495E-AE30-18FA64F51441"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12305.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_F561A746-01FA-463E-BF90-861A1F023EB2"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>The city shall be responsible for the design, construction, operation, and maintenance of the pedestrian mall and any related improvements, unless otherwise agreed to by the department.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)<span class="EnSpace"/>The department may enter into an agreement with the city to define roles and responsibilities, including maintenance, liability, and costs.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection><caml:LawSection id="id_53709F24-7245-408A-9B97-DA5156CCB83B"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>12306.</caml:Num><caml:LawSectionVersion id="id_7D04F798-EC4A-42D0-A447-B1387405EAF0"><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>This chapter shall not be construed to limit or supersede the authority of the department over the state highway system.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:LawSectionVersion></caml:LawSection></caml:LawHeading></caml:LawHeading></caml:Fragment></caml:BillSection><caml:BillSection id="id_79959816-3BC1-46D6-9F8C-F48577EDDAC3"><div style="margin:0 0 0.5em 0;"></div><caml:Num>SEC. 10.</caml:Num><caml:Content><p style="display:inline;"><s>The Legislature finds and declares that Sections 6 to 8, inclusive, of this act adding Sections 1814, 1815, and 1816 to the Streets and Highways Code address a matter of statewide concern rather than a municipal affair as that term is used in Section 5 of Article XI of the California Constitution. Therefore, Sections 6 to 8, inclusive, of this act apply to all cities, including charter cities.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></caml:Content></caml:BillSection></strike></font><div id="s100.3155173963147623"><div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SEC. 9.</i></font></h3> The Legislature finds and declares that providing a standardized process for approving pedestrian or bicycle safety projects is a matter of statewide concern and is not a municipal affair as that term is used in Section 5 of Article XI of the California Constitution. Therefore, Sections 6 to 8, inclusive, of this act adding Sections 1814, 1815, and 1816 to the Streets and Highways Code apply to all cities, including charter cities.</div></i></font></div></div><div id="s110.11867531836962675"><div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;"><font color="#B30000"><strike>SEC. 11.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>SEC. 10.</i></font></h3> If the Commission on State Mandates determines that this act contains costs mandated by the state, reimbursement to local agencies and school districts for those costs shall be made pursuant to Part 7 (commencing with Section 17500) of Division 4 of Title 2 of the Government Code.</div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
